<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-770-190  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 770 190.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  August 21 1990 v4 n29 p14(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>DataViz adds graphics translators, PC control option to MacLinkPlus. (DataViz Inc.'s MacLink Plus/PC 4.5 and MacLinkPlus/Translators utility programs) (includes related article onMacLink Plus 4.5.2 upgrade in October 1990) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wylie, Margie.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   DataViz Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   MacLink Plus/PC 4.5 (Utility program) (product introduction)MacLink Plus/Translators (Data conversion software) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionData ConversionUtility Programs.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Margie WylieandM;Boston -- Graphics translators and control from IBM PCs and compatibles, saidDataViz Inc., are the two biggest enhancements in Version 4.5 of itsMacLinkPlus file transfer and format-translation package.andM;In addition to translators previously available, Version 4.5 can convertgraphics files generated by several MS-DOS applications to PICT format.andO;Newly supported DOS file types include CGM files from Harvard Graphics andLotus Freelance Plus, WPG WordPerfect graphics files, IMG and GEM VenturaPublisher files, and AutoCAD DXF files.andP;  In addition, files from WordPerfectVersion 5.1 now can be translated to standard Mac word processing formatswith embedded graphics intact.andM;Aside from a PICT-to-PC Paintbrush translator, graphics can be translatedonly from PCs to Macs.andM;Text translators for MacWrite II and Microsoft Works (PC) are also in Version4.5, which is available now.andM;PC users can now fully control the transfer and translation process, whethervia serial cable or over a network, the company said.andP;  In the past, theprocess could be controlled only from the Mac.andM;The company also announced that its translation technology will be used inthe new Ventura Publisher, Macintosh Edition; and in Taste, a word processorforthcoming from DeltaPoint Inc.andM;Version 4.5 of MacLinkPlus/PC, for serial cable transfer, costs $199,including a cable.andP;  MacLinkPlus/Translators, for use with MacWrite II or theApple File Exchange utility on files transferred via network or SuperDrive,sells for $169.andP;  Customers who bought either package in the past 90 days canupgrade for $15; other registered users pay $45.andM;DataViz Inc. is located at 35 Corporate Drive, Trumbull, Conn.andP;  06611; (203)268-0030.andM;Even as they announced shipments of Version 4.5 of MacLinkPlus/PC andMacLinkPlus/Translators, officials of DataViz Inc. said another upgrade tothe file transfer and format-translation package is due in early October.andO;That release, Version 4.5.2, will add support for internal structures andlayout of translated documents, no matter what the source, so that users willbe able to bring over specialized text such as a table from a spreadsheetwithout losing the layout.andO;</TEXT></DOC>